  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240°C/ 220°C (fan)/ gas 9 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel the <strong>potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> and cut them into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel the <strong>garlic</strong> and finely slice 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> cloves (save the rest for later!)</p><p>Add the<strong> potatoes</strong> and<strong> sliced garlic</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> and <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> into small rough pieces</p><p>Chop the <strong>black olives</strong> roughly</p><p>Chop (or grate) the remaining<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong>,<strong> olives</strong> and <strong>garlic </strong>in a bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>-this is your<strong> tomato tapenade</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the<strong> basa</strong> <strong>fillets</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> pieces of <strong>baking paper</strong> or <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A3 sheets of paper</p><p>Lay each <strong>basa fillet</strong> in the middle of 2 pieces (doubling it up prevents any leakages!) and place on a baking tray</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> fish </strong>with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the<strong> fish </strong>evenly with the <strong>tomato tapenade</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the <strong>baking paper</strong> together around the<strong> fish</strong> to form a sealed parcel</p><p>Put the baking tray in the oven for 15 min or until the<strong> fish</strong> is cooked through</p><p>Tip: your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Pat the <strong>capers</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, carefully add the <strong>capers</strong> and cook for 1-2 min until they have puffed up a little, then transfer them to kitchen paper with a slotted spoon and set aside - these are your<strong> crispy capers</strong></p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim the <strong>asparagus spears</strong>,<strong> </strong>discarding the woody ends</p><p>Carefully remove the hot oil from the reserved pan and wipe it clean</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and once melted, add the <strong>asparagus</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a small splash of <strong>water</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 3 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>potatoes </strong>to a low heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of<strong> milk </strong>and mash until smooth</p><p>Remove the pot from the heat, add most of the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save some for garnish!) and mix to combine - this is your<strong> garlic and herb mash</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/730.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
